<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In this page : <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.filter.set.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a>
the code sample below:</p>

&lt;?php
$filter = new Zend_Filter_PregReplace(array('match' =&gt; 'bob',
                                            'replace' =&gt; 'john'));
$input  = 'Hy bob!";
 
$filter-&gt;filter($input);
// returns 'Hy john!'
?&gt;

<p>Contains 2 errors:
 - 'Hy bob!" begins with a single quote and ends with a double quote
 - 'match' =&gt; 'bob' triggers a "Delimiter must not be alphanumeric" error</p>

<p>Proposed fixed example:</p>

&lt;?php
$filter = new Zend_Filter_PregReplace(array('match' =&gt; '/bob/',
                                            'replace' =&gt; 'john'));
$input  = 'Hy bob!';
 
$filter-&gt;filter($input);
// returns 'Hy john!'
?&gt;

    </div>
